Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 10:56:43 +0100
Subject: (cherry-pick-branch-heads/7680) [M146] Reject frames with
 inconsistent U/V strides.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

All of openh264, libvpx and libaom seems to have issues with this. For
now, rejecting frames with this property. This should be seen as a
temporary workaround to be removed when the implementations have been
updated to support it.

(cherry picked from commit 5460d74631c9df16c9f0d160fb872c9834f8bb59)

